SIMPLE: likely
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Likely
<hw>Like"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Likelier</adjf> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧k"l⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Likeliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[That is,
<ets>like-like</ets>. See <er>Like</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Worthy of belief; probable; credible; <as>as, a
<ex>likely</ex> story</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It seems <qex>likely</qex> that he was in hope of being busy and
conspicuous.</q> <rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having probability; having or giving reason to
expect; -- followed by the infinitive; <as>as, it is <ex>likely</ex> to
rain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Similar; like; alike.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Such as suits; good-looking; pleasing; agreeable;
handsome.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au> <au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Having such qualities as make success probable; well
adapted to the place; promising; <as>as, a <ex>likely</ex> young man; a
<ex>likely</ex> servant.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Improbable; unlikely; -- used ironically; <as>as, a
<ex>likely</ex> story</as>.</def> <mark>[informal]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Likely</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Likely
<hw>Like"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In all probability;
probably.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While man was innocent he was <qex>likely</qex> ignorant of
nothing that imported him to know.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Like-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
